<% content_for(:title, "Calendars") %>

<div id="links-and-note">
  <div id="links">
    <p>You can view Gather calendars in your favorite calendar app:</p>

    <%= calendar_link("meals") %>
    <%= calendar_link("all_meals") %>
    <%= calendar_link("community_meals") if multi_community? %>
    <%= calendar_link("shifts") %>
    <%= calendar_link("reservations") %>
    <%= calendar_link("your_reservations") %>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <div>
      <h4><%= icon_tag("share-alt") %> A Note on Sharing</h4>
      Calendar links are tailored and unique to you, so don't share them. If you want to tell
      someone about this fun feature, send them the
      <%= link_to("link to this page", calendar_exports_path) %>,
      not an individual calendar.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="instructions">
  <h2>Instructions</h2>

  <h4><%= icon_tag("google") %> Google Calendar</h4>

  <ol>
    <li>Click 'Copy Link' above to copy the calendar URL to the clipboard.</li>
    <li>On the left of the Google Calendar screen, click the small down arrow next to 'Other Calendars'.</li>
    <li>Click 'Add by URL'.</li>
    <li>Paste the URL you copied above.</li>
    <li>Click 'Add Calendar'.</li>
    <li>The events should appear on your calendar after a few seconds.</li>
  </ol>

  <h4><%= icon_tag("apple") %> iCal</h4>

  <ol>
    <li>Click 'Copy Link' above to copy the calendar URL to the clipboard.</li>
    <li>Open iCal.</li>
    <li>Click the 'File' menu.</li>
    <li>Click 'Subscribe' or 'New Calendar Subscription'.</li>
    <li>Paste the URL you copied above.</li>
    <li>Click OK/Subscribe.</li>
    <li>Set subscription options if prompted. Recommended auto-refresh interval is 'every hour'.</li>
    <li>The events should now appear on your calendar.</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<div class="footnote">
  If you accidentally share your calendar links and want to make them private again,
  <%= link_to("click here to reset your secret token", reset_token_calendar_exports_path, method: :put) %>.
  Note: This will make the old links inoperative, so you will need to update your calendar app.
</div>
